Automation Testing Framework вЂ“ Design Document

 1. Project Overview

This project is a Selenium-based Automation Testing Framework developed using Java, TestNG, and Maven.
The framework automates key user workflows of the Automation Exercise website.



2. Objectives

* Automate login functionality (valid and invalid scenarios)
* Automate product search and add-to-cart flow
* Automate checkout process
* Capture screenshots for failed test cases
* Generate execution reports using Extent Reports



3. Framework Architecture

The framework follows the Page Object Model (POM) design pattern to ensure maintainability and reusability.

### Layers

*Base Layer

* Handles WebDriver initialization and teardown
* Manages browser setup and configuration

*Page Layer

* Contains page classes with web elements and actions
* Example: LoginPage, ProductPage, CartPage, CheckoutPage

*Test Layer

* Contains test cases and test logic
* Example: LoginTest

*Utility Layer

* ConfigReader: Reads configuration from properties file
* ExcelUtils: Reads test data from Excel file

*Listener Layer

* ExtentReportListener: Handles reporting and screenshot capture


  4. Test Scenarios

Test Case 1: Valid Login and End-to-End Flow

* Login using valid credentials
* Navigate to products page
* Search for a product
* Add product to cart
* View cart
* Proceed to checkout
* Place order

 Test Case 2: Invalid Login

* Attempt login with invalid credentials
* Verify error message is displayed
* Capture screenshot on failure

5. Technologies Used

* Java
* Selenium WebDriver
* TestNG
* Maven
* Apache POI (for Excel handling)
* Extent Reports

